net of things iot concussion risk management  litigation hydraulic fracturing msha  osha chemicals toxic tort litigation superfund  hazardous waste construction   industries – education hospitality  leisure mining trade associations technology media  telecommunications pharmaceuticals  life sciences energy chemicals   education university of california berkeley ba university of california hastings college of the law jd admissions california kevin c mayer partner los angeles san francisco kmayercrowellcom phone   south flower st th floorlos angeles ca 9 phone   embarcadero center th floorsan francisco ca 9 profile admissionsaffiliations highlights news  knowledge kevin c mayer is a partner and accomplished trial attorney with deep experience litigating on behalf of clients in a wide variety of complex commercial and mass tort actions he counsels clients facing regulatory enforcement at both the state and federal level he has litigated and tried cases in multiple federal state territorial and tribal courts as well as before government agencies and administrative bodies he is counselofrecord in some of the most important appellate decisions assisting the defense in tort litigation over the past  years his clients include members of the oil and chemical sporting goods and fitness energy medical device industrial and consumer products manufacturing and construction industries and academic institutions kevins trial record includes construction toxic tort osha environmental and products liability litigation he has particular experience addressing complex scientific medical and technical issues and preparing and examining expert witnesses in both deposition and trial settings for personal injury wrongful death and regulatory litigation kevin is a fellow of the litigation counsel of america the trial lawyers honor society and a muchsought speaker and author on litigation and trial practice he also serves on the firms public service committee kevin is dedicated to pro bono work and is a recipient of the  bet tzedek pro bono justice award for consistently providing counsel to eligible needy residents throughout los angeles county tort  products liability kevin is wellknown for his trial work on behalf of american and multinational companies in toxic tort and products liability litigation his experience includes evaluation of issues involving cancer systemic diseases birth defects dysmorphological and genetic consequences immune and endocrine system dysfunction and legionnaire’s disease toxic shock syndrome and other pathogenborne injuries his work emphasizes epidemiology pharmacology toxicology product labeling and warnings industrial hygiene regulatory compliance and process safety management kevins clients include upstream and downstream petroleum companies pharmaceutical and medical device manufacturers and the manufacturers and users of industrial commercial and consumergrade chemical and mineral products environmental kevin represents land owners and operators in federal cercla and rcra and state statutory and common law administrative proceedings litigation and trials involving environmental contamination costallocation leaking underground storage tanks waste disposal practices and commercial development his experience includes solid and liquid waste management regulatory compliance and enforcement superfund hydraulic fracturing fear of future disease risk assessment brownfields and soils air and groundwater contamination investigation and remediation regulatory enforcement kevin counsels clients and handles civil and administrative law trials and appeals for industrial and commercial entities alleged violations of the federal and states osha federal and state environmental statutes and regulations and californias safe drinking water and toxic enforcement act of 9 proposition  he has tried numerous osha citation appeals for refining and industrial facilities involving alleged violations of labor code and health  safety code standards for work place safety he counsels clients on proposition  statutory compliance and the emerging green chemistry regulations in california and throughout the country construction kevin represents national architectural and engineering firms developers contractors and facility owners in professional negligence premises liability construction defect and contract actions involving public works projects office buildings theaters athletic arenas and stadiums condominiums apartments and custom homes he serves as both plaintiff and defense counsel in these engagements traumatic brain injury since  kevin has developed particular experience on the tort liability issues arising from concussions and other traumatic brain injuries tbis associated with youth high school and collegiate athletics and has counseled multiple clients on the current state of medical and scientific knowledge concerning the diagnosis and treatment of tbis and return to play and return to classroom protocols kevin has delivered seminars and webinars on the legal aspects of tbi and has established relationships with some of the country’s most respected and sophisticated physicians and risk management experts on these issues notable engagements  serves as regional trial counsel for several major american chemical and products companies in toxic tort mass tort and asbestos litigation and works with national coordinating counsel on the clients medical and scientific evidentiary and expert witness issues represents one of the world’s largest art glass manufacturers in us epa and state proceedings involving hazardous air pollutants haps and potential violations of the federal clean air act serves as principal defense trial counsel for a medical device manufacturer being drawn into multiplaintiff federal and state court products liability lawsuits alleging design manufacturing and warnings defects fraudulent misrepresentation and concealment and breach of warranties served as defense trial counsel in toxic tort litigation involving claims of toxic shock syndrome transverse terminal limb reductions and legionnaire’s disease served as trial counsel for several chemical product manufacturers in three trial groups of dozens of plaintiffs alleging cancer and systemic disease from alleged exposures in lockheeds skunk works facilities in the lockheed worker coordinated judicial proceedings in los angeles handles proposition  notices investigations litigation and industrywide resolutions for myriad domestic and international companies whose products are alleged to contain excessive concentrations of various carcinogens and reproductive toxins including lead phthalates bisphenol a benzene and tdcpp represents a major hip resurfacing device manufacturer in litigating its civil claims and lawsuits including successful assertion of dispositive federal preemption defenses in the national hip implant litigation served as litigation and trial counsel for a large herbicide manufacturer in multidistrict litigation proceedings involving claims of property damage misbranding and mislabeling trial counsel for a major international generic pharmaceutical company in nationwide federal and state court litigation against the industry alleging medicaid overpayments for prescription drug reimbursements served as national coordinating counsel in the federal multidistrict litigation proceedings and defense liaison counsel in the coordinated california state court actions defending the formulators and encapsulators of nutritional supplements in the national ltryptophan products liability litigation served as a coordinating and litigation counsel for numerous product manufacturers and distributors in the new york minnesota and california ibm worker litigation addressing personal injury and wrongful death claims from cancer birth defects and other reproductive consequences represented the real estate development arm of a canadian conglomerate in construction defect litigation throughout california served as national trial and coordinating counsel for a major american company contesting claims of fraudulent misrepresentation concealment and conspiracy arising out of its historic investigative efforts research and publications on occupational hazards posed by exposure to industrial chemicals and minerals while in law school kevin was an extern to the honorable eugene f lynch us district court for the northern district of california  crowell  moring llp attorney advertising  prior results do not guarantee a similar outcome terms of use  privacy policy professionals practices  industries litigation  trial regulatory  policy transactions  corporate investigations industries news  events events firm news  announcements client alerts about leadership history case studies innovation in service diversity  inclusion pro bono careers   site map view mobile site locations washington dc new york los angeles san francisco orange county brussels london global experience find a professional a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z advanced search government experience contact     subscribe    alumni connect to us on linkedinfollow us on twitterfollow us on youtube lawyer kevin mayer  los angeles ca attorney  avvo skip to main content avvo requires javascript to function please enable javascript in your web browserhomefind a lawyercalifornialos angelesdefective and dangerous products attorneyskevin cooper mayerkevin cooper mayernot yet reviewedavvo rating    los angeles ca licensed since 9practice areasdefective and dangerous products litigation read more kevin cooper mayer call  aboutsimilar lawyersreviewscostcontactabout kevinpractice areasdefective and dangerous products unknown litigation see more lawyers resumelicensestatestatusacquiredupdatedcaactive9 we have not found any instances of professional misconduct for this lawyeravvo contributionslegal answerslegal guidesshow full resume  awardsaward namegrantordate grantedbest lawyers in americanasouthern californi